name: Balmoral Park
description: Bicycle track, kindergarten, sporting facilities, fitness circuit, skate park, recreation and bushland reserve, two playing fields, two synthetic wickets, cricket nets, night lighting on playing fields, carpark, toilets, seating and sailing club. Parking accessible to people with disabilities. Pay and display ticket parking.

name: Cartref Park
description: Small park, seating

name: Clifton Gardens
description: Adjoining Sydney Harbour National Park. Toilets, lots of trees, large open area, play equipment, basketball court, change rooms, seating, baths and wharf. Parking available (pay and display ticket area).

name: Countess Park
description: Street parking, children’s playground, gently sloping tree studded area with seating.

name: Curraghbeena Park
description: Street parking, seating, foreshore bushland reserve and play equipment.

name: Ellery Park
description: On-site interpretation works and signage relating to the history of the site and the orginal Spit Bridge, seating, viewing deck.

name: Hunter Park
description: Street parking, play equipment, seating, rest and recreation park, scattered trees and lawn area, sculpture The White Flower (by artist Chris Hodges) and Hunter Memorial. Toilets with disabled access on opposite side of The Esplanade.

name: Hunters Park
description: Seating, picnic tables, toilets

name: Little Ashton Park
description: Bushland, gardens and rock art. Free mulch available on Sundays 9am to 3pm. Limited access (no trailers please).

name: Memory Park

name: Mosman Park
description: Toilets at Allan Border Oval, cenotaph and memorial gardens, seating, basketball ring and street parking.

description: Carpark, foreshore walk, harbour frontage, rest park and bushland area, rowers’ club and marina.

name: Harnett Park
description: Carpark, foreshore walk, harbour frontage, rest park and bushland area, rowers’ club and marina.

description: Nature and bushland reserve with seating, lookout, bushwalking and street parking.

description: Walking track. Managed by National Parks and Wildlife Service.

description: Views, seating
